==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Procœlian
<hw>Pro*c⟦oe⟧"li*an</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Proc⟦oe⟧le</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Anat & Zool.)</fld> <def>Concave in
front; <as>as, <ex>proc⟦oe⟧lian</ex> vertebr⟦ae⟧, which have the
anterior end of the centra concave and the posterior
convex</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Procoelian</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Procœlian
<hw>Pro*c⟦oe⟧"li*an</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A
reptile having proc⟦oe⟧lian vertebr⟦ae⟧; one of the
Proc⟦oe⟧lia.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Procoelous</ent>⟦br⟧
